dcterms:description: The ADNI dataset provides resting state fMRI data collected from participants with Alzheimer's disease and various stages of mild cognitive impairment, facilitating research into biomarkers for Alzheimer's disease diagnosis.

dcterms:description: The AAL-116 template is used for automated anatomical labeling of brain regions in fMRI studies, providing a standardized framework for identifying regions of interest.

dcterms:description: The Latent Space Item Response Model (LSIRM) is used to map unobserved interactions between respondents and items, providing insights into the relationships among brain regions based on fMRI data.
dcterms:title: Latent Space Item Response Model (LSIRM)

dcterms:description: The continuous version of LSIRM adapts the original model to handle continuous data, allowing for the analysis of brain connectivity patterns in neuroimaging studies.
